<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-02-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="90" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Chang Yen Hoon</persName>
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Havana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-02-16"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 16,
                                    1889</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I respectfully inform you that the marriage of Chinese Emperor will be
                            celebrated twenty-eighth instant. I start for Washington on twentieth,
                            having been courteously entertained by American consul-general.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Chang Yen Hoon.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>